A California man gunned down his wife and her two children in their home on Monday night before turning the gun on himself, police believe.

Neighbors reported hearing the Fontana, California family arguing before the violence broke out.

The mother's oldest son, 16, went to the house to check on the family after he had failed to hear from them and found them dead, authorities said.

He discovered his mother and siblings, a 10-year-old boy and 12-year-old girl from a previous marriage, riddled with bullets. It was not clear how long they had been out of contact with the teen.

