A handgun was found and no suspect was being sought, police spokeswoman Martha Guzman-Hurtado said.

'Everything that has been confirmed so far indicates it could be a murder-suicide but that has not been confirmed,' Guzman-Hurtado said.

'They are questioning other people before making that conclusion.'

Neighbors told the KNBC-TV that they heard screaming and gunshots about 10pm following an argument in the house.

It appeared all four lived in the home, Sgt Imhof said. The victims appeared to be a family but identifications by the coroner are pending.

